{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5ba56577-b14b-498d-bb2b-db3b60a3bc25","content":"With **MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0**, Microsoft.Testing.Platform is already the **default**. You just need to:\n\n1. **Remove** (or set to `false`) the `<UseVSTest>` property in your project file:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Delete this line -->\n<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n```\n\nThat's it — no other SDK or package changes are needed.\n\n**Behavioral differences to be aware of:**\n\n- **Run tests** the same way: `dotnet test` works with both.\n- MSTest.Sdk already wires up the required `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` packages for you.\n- If you used any **VSTest-specific runsettings** (e.g., custom adapters), review them — some settings differ or aren't supported.\n- CLI flags change: e.g., filtering uses `--filter` with a slightly different syntax when running via `dotnet run -- --filter`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e203077f-04d0-4d99-899d-66a1d0f5b577","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in their MSTest project. This is a general knowledge question about .NET testing configuration. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.\n\nWhen using MSTest.Sdk, switching from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform involves:\n\n1. Removing `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` (or setting it to `false`) — Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the default in MSTest.Sdk 3.4+\n2. Adjusting how you run tests (using `dotnet test` or `dotnet run` depending on the version)\n\n\n3. Ensuring your project targets a compatible .NET version and has the necessary package references","outputTokens":390,"requestId":"3413:386D1F:5610BB5:5E33191:69F3FB18"},"id":"b270b51f-a9ff-40ca-a239-26f3e4453672","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:00:18.326Z","parentId":"49c36c10-4114-4194-a41b-f90a8b06076c"}
